Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Using a fork, prick @russet potato{2} all over. Wrap each potato in damp #paper towels{} and place on a #microwave-safe plate{}. Microwave, flipping halfway through, until potatoes are slightly softened, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Place tomato in a #small bowl{}; lightly season with @salt{}. Set aside until ready to serve.

Crush @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz} in bag.

Carefully cut a lengthwise slit into each microwaved potato, stopping about three-quarters of the way through.

> TIP: Make sure potatoes are still in one piece so you can easily wrap with foil before roasting.

Place each potato in the center of a piece of #foil{}; drizzle with @cooking oil{1%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Wrap with foil and place on a #baking sheet{}.

Roast on top rack until fork-tender, ~{20-22%minutes}.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

Meanwhile, on a second #baking sheet{}, toss broccoli with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @black pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While veggies roast, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #small pot{} (medium pot for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%oz} and scallion whites; season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Carefully drain any excess grease from pot.

Add @southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, @beef stock concentrate{1}, and @tomato paste{1} to pot with beef. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @water{1/2%cup} (1 cup for 4 servings). Reduce heat to medium. Cook, stirring occasionally, until most of the liquid has evaporated, ~{8-10%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Remove from heat; cover to keep warm.

Carefully remove potatoes from foil. Halve lengthwise; fluff insides with a fork. Top each with 1 TBSP @butter{4%tbsp} and sprinkle with @salt{}.

Serve potatoes, chili, broccoli, @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}, tomato, crushed tortilla chips, @sour cream{3%tbsp}, and scallion greens family style.

> Don't forget to serve with any extra items you may have ordered to build out your meal!